09 April - Cranberry Chutney 

- 1   cup water
- 3/4 cup sugar
- 12  oz cranberries
- 1   cup peeled and diced apples
- 1/2 cup vinegar
- 1/2 cup raisins
- 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon
- 1/4 teaspoon ginger
- 1/4 teaspoon allspice
- 1/8 teaspoon cloves


Combine water and sugar and bring to a boil over medium heat. Add cranberries, apples, and vinegar raisins and spices. Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes, stirring often while it's cooking. Pour mix in a bowl and wrap surface with plastic wrap. Cool to room temp, refrigerate.
